SIMPLE: tickseed
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tickseed
<hw>Tick"seed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Tick</ets>
the insect + <ets>seed</ets>; cf. G. <ets>wanzensamen</ets>, literally,
bug seed.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A seed or fruit resembling in shape an
insect, as that of certain plants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Same as
<er>Coreopsis</er>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Any plant of the genus
<gen>Corispermum</gen>, plants of the Goosefoot family.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ticktack</ent>⟦br⟧
